<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Celtic</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-16 12:47:46</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The best measure of value is to wear them and play with them for a while.  Personally I as an Enchanter don;t have a lot of HP so when I see Augmentation adding 19 AGI and 12 AC I try to keep it on myself all the time.  Especially since my pet wont go aggro until something takes a swing at me.  <BR>
<BR>
With the 19 AGI I find they swing at me and MISS a LOT more than they usual do.  With buffed AGI I seem to succeed in DODGING more perhaps this is factored into Dodging rolls too.  <BR>
<BR>
When they do hit me I still see them hitting for a lot even with the added 12 AC seems to make little difference.  The trick here is where you want your focus.  It makes no sense to have modest AGI and modest AC but you should probably decide WHICH you are going to shoot for.  If you are going for overpowering AC then you should go ALL OUT for AC and never trade it off for AGi because having no AGI gear in all other places then adding AGI gear on wrists at the cost of AC ensures the worst results because you WILL get hit a lot and the loss of AC to go from poor to below average AGI will not likely help matters.<BR>
<BR>
Has anyone else noticed there is a sinewave pattern to damage.  Where they hit with AC or whatever defensive advantages factored in like three times then on the fourth time Wham they hit for full damage.  Seems this BIG hit is like a BACK hit.  Point in case we are all running away from some mob and everyone reports the same damage 79 or whatever when hit in the back running away from Red mob.<BR>
<BR>
Likewise Warrior and Paladin are fighting together Warrior get hit for 4 hit for 4 hit for 4 them wham hit for 64.  Paladin gets hit for 11 hit for 8 hit for 11 then wham hit for 64.<BR>
<BR>
Seems like the mobs get a "Good" hit every fourth or fifth shot and the middle weak shot is if anything the lowest or zero or a miss.  This is also the time when they score weak hits you will also likely score weak hits.  I think this logic was added for casters to have a chance to get off a spell during the weakest zero damage misses you phase of battle so they can root and get out of range for the good hit.  Likewise a pair of tanks could time it so the most injured is backed away during the best hits and jumps back in closer for the weaker phase of combat to deal damage with minimal dmg taken.<BR>
<BR>
Back to the topic of Serp bracers.  They are nice but so much better gear around probably wind up getting resold later so dont pay too much.<BR>
<BR>
On the topic of Oh hey these are dirt cheap on server A and hard to find on Server B all depends on which groups have farmed them for how long on which servers to tip the scales of supply and demand.  There may be VERY few on one server and many people who want them and supply demand will drive the pricing.  Dont ya hate it when people try to manipulate and control prices?  I say find out who is interested in buying them maybe Monks and do a /Who Monk 12 24 ALL and send them each a tell saying you want to sell it and ask if they are interested and what would they offer you for it.  Write them all down and try again next evening at prime time.  This is the best way to find the right price on your server.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
